7. Dulichiae. Dulichium was one of the group of islands called Echinades, off the coast of Acamanta. Homer, 11.2.625, speaks of ‘Dulichium and the sacred islands Echinae. which lie beyond the sea, opposite to Etis? Strabo identifies Dulichium with one of the islands called Dolicha (Δολίχα) in his day. The island formed part of the kingdom of Ulysses, and was therefore probably the seat of the worship of his special patroness Pallas.
